  "prompt": "Are Kodak cameras still around?",
  "response": "Yes, Kodak continues to produce cameras, though their presence in the market has evolved significantly from their peak years. Today, Kodak offers a range of camera products that cater to various niches, including:\n\n1. **Digital Cameras:**\n   - **Compact Digital Cameras:** Kodak still manufactures compact digital cameras suitable for everyday photography. These are user-friendly and designed for casual photographers.\n   - **Action Cameras:** They offer rugged, waterproof action cameras aimed at adventure enthusiasts and those needing durable devices for outdoor activities.\n\n2. **Instant Cameras:**\n   - **Instant Film Cameras:** Following the resurgence of instant photography, Kodak has released instant cameras that print photos on the spot, similar to the popular Fujifilm Instax series. These cameras blend nostalgic appeal with modern features, appealing to both new users and photography enthusiasts.\n\n3. **Smartphone Accessories:**\n   - **Lens Attachments and Photo Printers:** While not traditional cameras, Kodak also offers accessories that enhance smartphone photography, such as clip-on lenses and portable photo printers.\n\n4. **Specialized Imaging Products:**\n   - Kodak maintains a presence in certain specialized imaging sectors, providing products tailored for specific professional or hobbyist needs.\n\n**Availability:**\nKodak cameras and related products are available through various online retailers, electronics stores, and directly from their official website. While they may not compete directly with major digital camera brands like Canon, Nikon, or Sony in terms of market share and advanced features, Kodak maintains a loyal customer base by focusing on simplicity, affordability, and nostalgic appeal.\n\n**Brand Licensing:**\nIn some cases, Kodak licenses its brand to other manufacturers who produce cameras and imaging products on their behalf. This strategy allows Kodak to maintain a presence in the camera market without handling all aspects of production and distribution themselves.\n\nIn summary, while Kodak may not dominate the camera industry as it once did, the company still offers a variety of camera products that cater to different segments, ensuring that the Kodak name remains associated with photography and imaging.",
